# Frontend Conventions (React + Vite + TypeScript)

## Stack
- React 18, Vite, TypeScript. Entry: `frontend/src/main.tsx`. Router in `App.tsx`.
- Routing: `react-router-dom`. Non-home routes (`/about`, `/opening-analyzer`, etc.) render `ComingSoonPage`.
- Global stylesheet: `frontend/src/styles/global.css` (single file, ~30 KB — CSS Modules is a future migration).

## Type safety
- Every field in Flask's `/generate` `response_data` dict must have a matching type in `frontend/src/types/stats.ts`.
- Run `npm run typecheck` in `frontend/` before committing any TypeScript change.

## Dev workflow
- Two processes: `python app.py` (:5001) + `cd frontend && npm run dev` (:5173).
- Vite proxies `/generate`, `/api/*`, `/static/*` to Flask — no CORS config needed locally.
- For production-mode testing: `cd frontend && npm run build` → `python app.py` → http://localhost:5001.

## Static assets
- Generated chart PNGs live in `static/images/` (gitignored, regenerated per request).
- Permanent assets (`background.jpg`, `gift2.png`, etc.) are in `static/` and served by Flask at `/static/*`.
- Reference them by URL (`/static/background.jpg`), not by import.

## Image export (html2canvas)
- `captureRef` is on `.stats-capture-inner` (profile header + stat grid only).
- Background color inferred from the element; falls back to `#2d6056` if transparent.
- Do not re-add `applyExportStyles` / `restoreStyles` — these were removed intentionally.

## Heroku build
- Node buildpack must be listed **before** Python.
- `NPM_CONFIG_PRODUCTION=false` must be set so `devDependencies` (tsc, vite) are installed.
- Node version pinned to `20.x` in both `package.json` files.
